      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "This release focuses on sync reliability — hidden files, interrupted syncs, and protecting your notes from wrong deletions.\n\n## Fixed\n\n- **Hidden / config files now sync reliably.** Dot-prefixed paths (`.obsidian`, `.airsync`, and nested folders like `foo/.bar`) are excluded from Obsidian's in-memory index, which made them get re-detected every cycle and never converge. They're now read and written through the raw adapter, so they sync to completion. (A hidden path still only syncs when you enable *Sync dot paths* and it isn't ignored.)\n- **Interrupted syncs recover instead of getting stuck on \"Synced\".** Quitting mid-sync — or a cycle with a failed action — could leave the vault half-synced while the status still read *Synced*. The delta cursor is now committed only after a fully successful cycle, and the next run forces a full reconcile to rediscover anything left behind.\n- **Folder renames no longer trigger spurious deletes.** Renaming a folder on the remote could strand the moved files and resurrect them on a later sync. Renames now rewrite baselines to the new path; if the destination is already occupied, the bulk rename is skipped and files converge one by one.\n- **Erroneous deletions are now prevented structurally.** The old volume-based safety check — which could silently drop a legitimate single-file deletion — is replaced by authoritative local-absence checks, gated on the workspace being fully loaded, so a file missing only from a half-loaded index is never deleted. Genuine deletions still propagate.\n\n## Added\n\n- **\"Rescan vault\" action** in settings to force a full reconcile on demand.\n\n## Internal\n\n- Hardened test harness (decision-table suite, convergence/conflict tests, coverage gates) and lint guards enforcing the architecture's design principles.\n",
